<TITLE> Charges framed against Barisal mayor </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 5 (bdnews24.com)A special tribunal in Dhaka Sunday framed charges against Barisal mayor Majibor Rahman Sarwar in an arms case. Judge Nuruzzaman of Dhaka Metropolitan Special Tribunal-7 framed the charges against Sarwar, while he claimed that he was innocent. Joint forces arrested the mayor at his Gulshan home in Dhaka on May 28 and retrieved four revolver bullets possessed illegally. Akteruzzaman, a RAB officer, filed a case against Sarwar on June 18 with Gulshan Police Station under the Arms Act. Police sub-inspector Shahidullah submitted a chargesheet in the case against Sarwar on July 17. bdnews
